<html>
	<head>
		<title>Replace Dialog</title>
		<meta http-equiv="Content-Language" content="en-us">
		<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=windows-1252">
	</head>
	<body>
		<p><img border="0" src="replace.jpg"></p>
		<p>This is the replace dialog. With it you can search for each occurence of a 
			combination of characters replacing it by another combination of characters. In 
			the dialog as displayed above you have the following possibilities:</p>
		<table border="1" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellPadding="2" ID="Table1">
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Find what</td>
				<td width="65%">This combo-box control contains a small history of character strings 
					you have searched for. You can either select one of these strings or type in a 
					new one.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">
					Replace with</td>
				<td width="65%">
					This combo-box control contains a small history of character strings you have 
					used to replace other characters strings. You can either select one of these 
					strings or type in a new one.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">
					Match whole words only</td>
				<td width="65%">When this option is checked you look for whole words only. This means 
					that when you look for the word "hello" you will find it in text like "hello 
					world" but not in text like "hello-world".
				</td>
			</tr>
			<TR>
				<TD width="35%">Match case</TD>
				<TD width="65%">When this option is checked case is also checked.</TD>
			</TR>
			<TR>
				<TD width="35%">Replace in</TD>
				<TD width="65%">Here you have two possibilities. When <B>Selection</B> is checked the 
					search/replace only takes place in the current selection. When <B>Whole text</B>
					is checked the search/replace takes place in the whole text.</TD>
			</TR>
			<TR>
				<TD width="35%">Find Next</TD>
				<TD width="65%">When you click on this button the next occurence of the character 
					sequence is looked up.</TD>
			</TR>
			<TR>
				<TD width="35%">Replace</TD>
				<TD width="65%">When you click on this button the currently found occurence of the 
					character sequence is replaced by the given character combination. If there is 
					no found character sequence clicking this button will search for the given 
					sequence.</TD>
			</TR>
			<TR>
				<TD width="35%">Replace All</TD>
				<TD width="65%">When you click on this button all occurences of the character sequence 
					matching the one you are looking for are replaced by the given character 
					sequence.</TD>
			</TR>
			<TR>
				<TD width="35%">Cancel</TD>
				<TD width="65%">Aborts the operation.</TD>
			</TR>
		</table>
		<dl>
			<dt>&nbsp;</dt>
		</dl>
	</body>
</html>
